To calculate the Current Assets Turnover Ratio, we use the formula:

Current Assets Turnover Ratio = Net Revenue / Average Current Assets

Step 1: Identify Net Revenue (from income statement)  
Total Revenue = 5,064,939.23

Step 2: Calculate Average Current Assets  
Initial Current Assets (at 2023-12-31) = 8,000,000.00  
Ending Current Assets (at 2024-01-29) = 9,717,259.46  

Average Current Assets = (8,000,000.00 + 9,717,259.46) / 2  
= 17,717,259.46 / 2  
= 8,858,629.73

Step 3: Calculate Current Assets Turnover Ratio  
= 5,064,939.23 / 8,858,629.73
